<h1 class="title is-2">Wind Chill Calculator</h1>
<p class="subtitle is-5 mt-3">
  A simple weather tool that shows how cold it actually feels.
</p>

<div class="box extra-box">

  <div class="field">
    <label class="label">Temperature (°C)</label>
    <input class="input" type="number" placeholder="e.g. 5">
  </div>

  <div class="field">
    <label class="label">Wind Speed (km/h)</label>
    <input class="input" type="number" placeholder="e.g. 20">
  </div>

  <div class="notification is-light mt-4">
    <p class="has-text-weight-semibold">Wind Chill Formula:</p>
    <p class="mt-2">
      WC = 13.12 + 0.6215T − 11.37V<sup>0.16</sup> + 0.3965T V<sup>0.16</sup>
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 is-size-7">
      where T is temperature (°C) and V is wind speed (km/h)
    </p>
  </div>

  <p class="mt-4">
    This formula is used by meteorological services to estimate how cold the
    weather feels on exposed skin.
  </p>

</div>
